@node RNC " RNC UNPACKER command        "

RNC UNPACKER - it decrunch all files that MVR use ...

format * {RNC?m{command}}

        m - unpacking method (1 or 2)
        command - tells unpacker what kind of file he's gona decrunch
                  (PIC, MOD, TXT, FNT) 

example:
{RNC?1{PIC?ILBM?PIC/PIC001.Iff}}           
                                                   

@endnode

@node PAL " PAL command        "

Set palette for the text screen (only 16 colors).
Don't use it after SCR.

format * {PAL?col0,col1,...,col15}

        coln - where n is number of color (in this case only 16 colors
                                           avaible) 
example:

{PAL?$000,$f00,$fff,,,$be7}

@endnode

@node RET " RET command        "

Like TXT but also jump to page. (!!! Use it only with ZON command!!!)

format * {RET?page?name}

        page - number of text page that you wish to jump
        name - name and path for the text that need to be show

Example:

{RET?15?text/text.13}
        
@endnode

@node JMP " JMP command        "

Jump to page. (!!! Use it only with ZON command !!!)

format * {JMP?page}

        page - number of page to jump to

example:

{JMP?12}

@endnode

@node ZON " ZON command        "

Make zone around the text.
When user clik on the zone then ZON call command and execute it.

format * {ZON?text,{command}}

        text    - text that'll be in the zone
        command - use only PIC, MOD, TXT, JMP, RET, RNC commands.

example:

{ZON?Click me,{PIC?ILBM?PIC/PIC001.Iff}}

@endnode

@node COL " COL command        "

Set pen and paper colours.

format * {COL?n?m}

        n - pen color 0-15
        m - paper color 0-15

example:

{COL?5?0}
 
@endnode

@node CEN " CEN command        "

ALL text after this command will be centred.
Don't use multicolor text line when using this command or MVR will ignore
all others and use just the last one.

format * {CEN}

example:

{CEN}

@endnode

@node GRF " GRF command        "

Print graphics font on the screen.

format * {GRF?text}

        text - text that you wish to be displayed.

example:

{GRF?Welcome to MVR}

        NOTICE: MVR use only UPPERCASE letters.
                (Example will look like this "WELCOME TO MVR", so no
                 lower case letters in this command because they'll
                 be displayed as UPPERCASE letters).

@endnode

@node FNT " FNT command        "

Load graphics font (picture).

format * {FNT?format?size?name}

        format - you can use three picture formats:
                  ILBM - iff format
                  AMBK - amos format
                  MRAW - MAD VIRGIN FORMAT
        size   - 8,16,32 (size in pixels x i y)
        name   - path and name of file

example:

{FNT?ILBM?16?FONTS/MVR.FNT}

@endnode

@node TXT " TXT command        "

Load MVR text file (ASCII). Use it only with ZON command.

format * {TXT?name}

        name - name and path of desired text file.
               
example:

{TXT?TEXT/TEXT.24}

@endnode

@node MOD " MOD command        "

Load and play music. Use like PIC instruction 

format * {MOD?format?name}

        format - you can use three differnt type of modules    
                 PROT - pro/sound tracker module
                 TMMC - MAD VIRGIN module
                 AMBK - AMOS music bank
        name - name and path of module you wish to play.

example:

{MOD?PROT?MODS/BRIDGE.MOD}

@endnode

@node PIC " PIC command        "

Load picture and display it on the screen and wait for mouse click.
Use this command alone or with ZON.

format * {PIC?format?name}
        format - ILBM - iff format
                 AMBK - amos format
                 MRAW - MAD VIRGIN FORMAT
        name - path and name of file

example:

{PIC?ILBM?PICS/CABLE.IFF}

@endnode

@node END " END command        "

This instruction must exist on the end of any text files used with MVR.
(config file and text files called from MVR)

format * {END}

example:

{END}

@endnode

@node SCR " SCR command        "

Activate direct mode and write all tekst on the screen.

format * {SCR}

example:

{SCR}

@endnode

@node EFF " Effect commands        "

Activate effect for screen appearing.

format * {EFn}

        n - number of effect (for now only six effects avaible) 1-6

example:

{EF3}

        NOTICE: When you wish to turnoff effect on the end of the
                page so it wouldn't still be activated you need
                to put before END command new command which will
                turn off effect and that is NOE
@endnode
